cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use brainstorm-mode in your research or tooling, please cite it."
title: "brainstorm-mode: Enforceable Ideation Mode for AI Coding Agents"
abstract: >-
  A Claude Code plugin and multi-agent framework that enforces brainstorm mode
  in AI coding agents. It blocks file-editing tools at the hook layer and
  re-injects the brainstorming constraint on every prompt so it survives context
  compaction, countering execution drift — the tendency of instruction-tuned
  coding agents to abandon ideation and begin implementing. Includes drift-log
  instrumentation for measuring execution-drift rate over a session.
type: software
